THW implement the 50+1 rule in all franchise cricket (IPL, Big Bash, LPL)In the context of the "50+1" rule in German football, the term "members'' refers to supporters or fans of a football club who join the club as official members by paying an annual fee or subscription
Under the "50+1" rule, these members collectively own at least 50% plus one share of the club, ensuring that they maintain majority control over important decisions such as the election of club officials, financial matters, and the overall direction of the club.
This structure is designed to prioritize the interests of the supporters and maintain the club's connection to its local community.
